Cell.Data: Data being read from SR1 and compliment stored in DR
NOT operation and SR1 register is being used
bits [11:9] of LDR instruction used to determine the destination register of the data loaded
bits [8:6] of LDR instruction used to determine the starting point from which to offset to find the register being loaded from
bits [5:0] of LDR instruction used to determine the register address to load from based on BaseR
bits [11:9] of LDI instruction used to determine the destination register of the data loaded
bits [8:0] of LDI instruction used to determine the register address to load from based on PC
bits [11:9] of LD instruction used to determine the destination register of the data loaded
bits [8:0] of LD instruction used to determine the register address to load from based on PC
The offset operand of BR in bits [8:0] to determine pcoffset9
JMP uses the correct BaseR at [8:6] as source of NPC
BR useed NZP field bits of [11:9] for condition
JMP instructions have all valid combinations of BaseR
BR instructions have all valid combinations of NZP including: 011, 001, 101, 010
BR instructions have all valid pcoffset9
